cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper proposes a deep learning approach to estimate foot pressure maps from 2D human pose derived from video, which can aid in stability analysis in fields such as kinesiology, medicine, and robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training a convolutional neural network, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the application of the proposed method in fields such as kinesiology and robotics suggests that it may also belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) and cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper involves collecting and analyzing data, which may fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
